<task id="043" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D3-04 Operator-led end-to-end testing (discoverability + correctness pass across 7 high-readiness surfaces)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 day</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>Operator — Claude Code assists as walkthrough/checklist runner + evidence compiler</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 3 — Polish + Future-Use Validation</phase>
    <wave>P3-3 (serial; runs after 040 + 041 + 042 complete; blocks 044 lessons-learned)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>040 (D3-01 `/analyze` proof point), 041 (D3-02 Get Started welcome card), 042 (D3-03 telemetry dashboards)</dependencies>
    <tags>operator-led, testing, e2e, discoverability</tags>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Run an operator-led end-to-end testing pass against the R5-shipped SpaarkeAi
    surface on Spaarke Dev. Test along TWO axes — **discoverability** (can a user
    find the capability without prompting?) and **correctness** (does it behave as
    specified once invoked?) — across the seven high-readiness surfaces called out
    in the R5 user-testing kickoff doc (`notes/user-testing-kickoff.md`) and the
    `notes/ground-truth-spaarkeai-state.md` §7 "Suggested initial test focus":

    1. **Workspace switching** — dropdown + auto-install + pinned + tab persistence + custom layouts (FR carry-over from R3/R4; R5 left this surface untouched, but it is the most-used entry point and must regress-pass).
    2. **Attachment uploads** — 25 MB binary cap, MIME allow-list, end-to-end chat + file association (per `docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md`; R5 extends this with `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` manifest from task 004).
    3. **Section picker** — WorkspaceLayoutWizard "+ New Workspace" → picker shows all 7 sections including Calendar + Daily Briefing; compose + save + reopen.
    4. **Pane collapse** — click any pane header to collapse to icon-only strip; click strip to re-expand; state persists across refresh; all three panes independently collapsible (R4 task 094 shipped this).
    5. **Chat + playbook lifecycle** — chat session creation → message exchange → playbook invocation (e.g., Predict Matter Cost) → response rendering → session close + restoration on next visit (R5 left the chat lifecycle intact; this is a regression pass).
    6. **W-4 / W-5 concept validation (NOW REAL — was partial in R4)** — Assistant → Workspace mount (W-4: DocumentViewerWidget dispatcher wiring shipped by task 022) AND Context → Workspace mount (W-5: per-wizard final-step "Add to Workspace" handlers). Concept validation now testable end-to-end (where R4 left them as "infrastructure-only" caveats).
    7. **NEW Summarize + Insights tool integration** — Slash command `/summarize` + natural-language tool routing → `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` progressive rendering → `FilePreviewContextWidget` preview → Insights `insights.query` tool (playbook + RAG paths) → `InsightsResponseRenderer` + clickable citations + confidence floor badge.

    This is a **PURE TEST + DOCUMENTATION** task — ZERO production code change. The
    AI agent does NOT drive the SpaarkeAi UI; the **operator** does. Claude Code
    serves as the walkthrough/checklist runner: it surfaces each surface's expected
    discoverability cues + correctness assertions verbatim from the spec / kickoff
    doc, prompts the operator to exercise the surface on Spaarke Dev tenant,
    captures findings via the operator's spoken/typed observations, ranks findings
    by severity (Blocking / High / Medium / Low) using the rubric defined in Step 4
    below, and compiles everything into the ONE deliverable
    `notes/testing-pass-results.md`.

    The output of this task feeds task 044 (D3-05 lessons-learned + R6 backlog) —
    High and Medium findings populate the R6 backlog; Blocking findings escalate
    immediately and gate task 044. Low findings inform polish backlog without
    blocking. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code touched; confirm in
    results doc).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Operator-led testing facilitator. The OPERATOR is the user-testing driver —
    they exercise the SpaarkeAi UI on Spaarke Dev tenant, observe behavior, and
    speak/type observations. Claude Code is the walkthrough assistant — it does
    NOT make UI clicks (no browser automation in this task), does NOT judge UX
    independently. Its job is to:

    1. Load the seven surface specs verbatim from `spec.md` / `notes/user-testing-kickoff.md` / `notes/ground-truth-spaarkeai-state.md`.
    2. Surface each surface's expected discoverability cues + correctness assertions one at a time.
    3. Prompt the operator with a structured per-surface walkthrough script.
    4. Capture operator observations as paraphrased text (no verbatim customer-data quotes; Spaarke Dev is synthetic, but the discipline is reinforced).
    5. Rank each finding per the Step 4 severity rubric.
    6. Compile the consolidated `notes/testing-pass-results.md` at the end.
    7. Flag Blocking findings to the operator immediately for escalation (do NOT silently log).

    Claude Code is competent on the platform — familiar with R5 spec, kickoff doc,
    ground-truth doc, R4 lessons-learned, and the seven surface implementations.
    It is NOT a QA automation harness — it is a structured-walkthrough coach.
  </role>

  <goal>
    ONE concrete deliverable on the R5 branch:

    **`projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/testing-pass-results.md`** (NEW, ephemeral notes)

    Contents:
    1. Test session metadata — date, tenant (Spaarke Dev), operator identity (e.g., "Ralph Schroeder"), Wave F deployment status at test time (per `notes/insights-r2-coordination.md` §8 changelog), session duration.
    2. Per-surface walkthrough record (7 sections, one per surface above). Each section captures:
       - Discoverability axis: was the entry point findable without prompting? (yes / partial / no, paraphrased rationale).
       - Correctness axis: did the surface behave per spec? (pass / partial / fail, paraphrased per-assertion outcomes).
       - Findings filed against this surface (linked to the ranked findings list in §3 below).
    3. Consolidated findings list, ranked by severity (Blocking / High / Medium / Low) per the Step 4 rubric. Each finding has: ID (FIND-NNN), surface, axis (discoverability / correctness / both), severity, paraphrased description, suggested remediation owner (R5 patch / R6 backlog / R5 lessons-learned doc note only).
    4. Aggregate verdict per surface (regression / pass / partial / fail).
    5. Aggregate verdict for the testing pass overall (Phase 3 ship-ready / Phase 3 ship-with-followups / Phase 3 ship-blocked-on-finding-X).
    6. Confirmations: BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB; zero new dependencies; no production code change.
    7. Cross-link to task 044 R6 backlog seed list (High + Medium findings) for downstream consumption.

    Acceptance: ALL seven surfaces walked through; findings captured + ranked;
    `testing-pass-results.md` exists with the seven structured sections + ranked
    findings; ZERO unresolved Blocking findings (or, if Blocking is present, it is
    explicitly escalated to the operator with a recorded next-step + the task is
    BLOCKED-PENDING-ESCALATION until resolved).
  </goal>

