  <constraints>
    <constraint source="plan.md D3-04">Discoverability + correctness pass per kickoff doc's high-readiness surfaces (workspace switching, attachment uploads, section picker, pane collapse, chat + playbook lifecycle, W-4/W-5 concept validation now that they're real, NEW Summarize + Insights tool integration). Output: `notes/testing-pass-results.md`. Findings synthesized + ranked by severity.</constraint>
    <constraint source="plan.md Phase 3 gating">Phase 3 ships when: operator-led end-to-end testing complete; lessons-learned authored. This task (043) is the operator-led testing step; task 044 is the lessons-learned step. Both must close before project wrap-up (task 090).</constraint>
    <constraint source="kickoff doc §"High readiness"">The seven high-readiness surfaces are the binding test scope. Lower-readiness surfaces (W-4/W-5 in R4 were "partial"; R5 made them real via task 022 dispatcher wiring + task 017/018 widget surface) are NOW in scope per kickoff doc's "now that they're real" qualifier. Test recommendation in ground-truth doc §7 specifically calls out the W-4/W-5 + chat lifecycle as fair game once R5 ships them.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (operator-led)">This task is testing/QA. Claude Code is a guided walkthrough; operator drives actual testing on Spaarke Dev. NO browser automation in this task — operator clicks, observes, speaks/types. Claude Code captures + structures + ranks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (severity ranking — binding)">Findings ranked Blocking / High / Medium / Low per the Step 4 rubric. Blocking = contract violation, data loss, security issue, or "Phase 3 ship cannot proceed". High = major UX gap, regression, broken happy-path. Medium = polish gap, minor UX rough edge, R6 backlog candidate. Low = nice-to-have, observation-only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 / ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (this task adds notes only; no production code change; no `dotnet publish` measurement required). Confirm in results doc.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018 (no information leakage)">Even on Spaarke Dev synthetic data, evidence is paraphrased — NO verbatim citations / answer text / customer-data-shaped content in `testing-pass-results.md`. Operator observations captured as structural + categorical, not as raw quotes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec SC-22">Lessons-learned + R6 backlog produced per phase wrap-up (task 044 D3-05). High + Medium findings from this task seed that backlog; cross-link explicitly in §7 of results doc.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (Wave F state recording)">Wave F (Insights v1.1 SSE + clickable citations `href`) deployment status MUST be recorded in results doc metadata. If Wave F shipped, test the v1.1 paths (SSE streaming + clickable `href` citations). If Wave F NOT shipped, test the v1.0 fallback paths (single-shot + display-name-only citations). Either is contract-acceptable per NFR-11 graceful fallback.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (Blocking escalation)">If a Blocking finding is observed during the walkthrough, the walkthrough PAUSES — the operator decides immediately whether to (a) continue testing other surfaces with the Blocking issue flagged for parallel remediation, OR (b) STOP the testing pass and escalate. Either choice is captured in results doc §5 (aggregate verdict).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (zero-code-change)">This task touches ZERO `.cs`, `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.bicep`, `.json` (other than the results notes file). If the testing pass surfaces a Blocking finding that requires immediate code fix, that fix is a SEPARATE follow-up task (not bundled into task 043). Task 043 captures the finding and unblocks itself by handing the fix to a new ticket.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 / reuse mandate">No parallel test infrastructure created. No new test fixtures. No new docs templates. The results doc follows the existing R5 `notes/` markdown convention. The walkthrough script is inline in Step 3 of this POML — NOT a separate file.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>operator-led-testing/discoverability-correctness-pass</topic>
    <files>
